case_circumstances:
On August 19, 1971 the body of a white female was discovered in a wooded area directly off of the Redwood Highway in Josephine County, near the Oregon-California border.  She was fully clothed and had distinctive jewelry; please see the "Clothing and Accessories" tab for a description of all items found with the decedent.

For additional information go to  www.antique-jewelry-investor.com/crime-scene-investigation.html
